    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "     2. Línea Abierta: From Victim to Leader: (2013)"
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "url": "https://americanarchive.org/catalog/cpb-aacip-a654dc31a04",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "https://americanarchive.org/catalog/cpb-aacip-a654dc31a04"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "          Listen from minute 6:48 to 57:52, where the host interviews domestic violence activist María Hernández and Andrea Cristina Mercado. María is the   "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "          domestic violence program coordinator at Mujeres Unidas y Activistas. Cristina is the campaign director of the National Domestic Workers Alliance. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "          [Disclaimer: This podcast includes discussions on sensitive topics, such as domestic violence. Listener discretion is advised.]"
        }
      ]
